org.efaps.db.transaction

Class AbstractResource

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.efaps.db.transaction.AbstractResource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    XAResource
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractStoreResource, ConnectionResource

    public abstract class AbstractResource
extends Object
implements XAResource
    Abstract class used to given an easy interface to implemented XA resources within the eFaps application.
    To use the implementation of such resource, it must be called first method open(). To free a resource of using, methods commit() (if all work was OK) or abort() (if the transaction must be rolled back) must be called.
    Version:
    $Id$
    Author:
    The eFaps Team

      • commit

        public void commit()
            throws EFapsException
        Closes this connection resource and delisted this resource in the transaction. The method must be called if the transaction should be commited.
        Throws:
        EFapsException - if the resource is not opened or this resource could not delisted

      • abort

        public void abort()
           throws EFapsException
        Closes this XA resource and delisted this resource in the transaction.
        The method must be called if the transaction should be aborted (rolled back).
        Throws:
        EFapsException - if the resource is not opened or this resource could not delisted

      • isSameRM

        public boolean isSameRM(XAResource _xares)
        The method is called from the transaction (manager) to check if the XA resource is the same as the given XA resource in the parameter _xaras. This is done with a string compare (method String.equals(Object)) off the Object.toString() methods of this and the XA resource in _xaras.
        Specified by:
        isSameRM in interface XAResource
        Parameters:
        _xares - XA resource used to test if same resource
        Returns:
        true if the string compare returns that they are equal, otherwise false is returned
